<title>USA: Price Waterhouse tops workplace list for computer experts.</title>
<headline>Price Waterhouse tops workplace list for computer experts.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK</dateline>
<text>
<p>Auditors Price Waterhouse LLP tops the list of the 100 best places to work in the information systems field, according to Computerworld newspaper.</p>
<p>&quot;Without skilled IS professionals, business wouldn't be able to function, let alone compete effectively,&quot; the weekly newspaper for information systems management said.</p>
<p>Price Waterhouse topped the list of the best 100 companies out of a field of about 1,000 firms surveyed.</p>
<p>&quot;This year's Best Places to Work companies proved a well-rounded working environment for IS employees, which includes low turnover, emphasis on training, diverse staffing and growth opportunities,&quot; said Joyce Chutchian-Ferranti, a managing editor in Computerworld's magazine group.</p>
<p>&quot;Some companies may excel in some areas more than others, but it's the subtle, innovative ways that these companies combine business, technology and cultural issues that inspire employees to work at these companies,&quot; she said.</p>
<p>Computerworld's ranking of the top 10 places to work:</p>
<p>1. Price Waterhouse LLP, New York</p>
<p>2. Tech Data Corp., Clearwater, Fla.</p>
<p>3. Solectron Corp., Malpitas, Calif.</p>
<p>4. The Home Depot Inc., Atlanta, Ga.</p>
<p>5. Computer Associates International Inc., Islandia, N.Y.</p>
<p>6. Capital One Services Inc., Glen Allen, Va.</p>
<p>7. Southwest Airlines Co., Dallas, Texas</p>
<p>8. Dayton Hudson Corp., Minneapolis, Minn.</p>
<p>9. Wal-Mart Stores Inc., Bentonville, Ark.</p>
<p>10. Xerox Corp., Stamford, Conn.</p>
